[4] Philippines (Metro Manila)
Date: Thu 8 Oct 2009
Source: Manila Bulletin [edited]
<http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/223834/no-dengue-outbreak-cavite-health-exec>


The Cavite Provincial Health Office tagged as false a report that there is
dengue epidemic in Dasmarinas town. Sanitary inspector Anabelle R Dilig
made the clarification amid a report that there were 5 dengue deaths in the
province's most populated town. "While it is true that there were 5 dengue
deaths in Dasmarinas, the report that there is a dengue outbreak in the
town is false. The epidemic threshold can attest to this," said Dilig.

The Dasmarinas Health Office confirmed earlier that the dengue fatalities
in the town are 3 children, a 9 month old baby, and a 38 year old man. The
victims are residents of Barangays [smallest administrative division] San
Dionisio, Victoria Reyes, Zone III, Paliparan I, and City Homes in Langkaan
II, it was gathered. Dilig said to sum it all, there are 80 dengue cases,
including the 5 deaths, in Dasmarinas during the August-September [2009]
period. "The fact is we were able to contain the disease before it reached
alarming proportion," said the provincial dengue coordinating officer.

Dilig claimed that the epidemic threshold or the examination and survey
made in the last 5 years will decide if there is a dengue outbreak in the
town. Dlig said the provincial health office is doing everything to check
the dengue cases not only in Dasmarinas town but the whole of Cavite.

[byline: Anthony Giron]

