[5] Dominican Republic
Date: Fri 25 Sep 2009
Source: La Nacion Dominicana, Prensa Latina report [in Spanish, trans.
Mod.TY, edited]
<http://lanaciondominicana.com/ver_noticia.php?id_noticia=12338&sesion_periodico=24>


A baby of 7 months raised to 3 the list of DHF deaths in the Dominican
Republic in the past 2 weeks, according to a medical report released today
[25 Sep 2009]. The child was admitted into hospital in his home province of
Santiago (in northern DR), days ago, suffering the disease, which is
endemic in Central America and the Caribbean. The physicians' efforts were
not sufficient to save his life.

This is the 2nd minor [age child] who died of the same cause in this
province in the last 7 days and the 3rd in the country, according to
official statistics.

Health media urged authorities to launch an awareness campaign about the
disease and the population to adopt domestic sanitary measures to avoid
proliferation of the mosquito vector that transmits the disease [virus].

A source in the hospital where the child had been admitted said that there
were more children admitted for the same cause [disease], but declined to
give precise figures and details about how many were affected with the same
type of disease.

The most visible direct cause of the dengue outbreak in the Cibao region
[the whole northern part of the Dominican territory] is the [accumulation]
of stagnant water from the copious rains that have fallen in recent weeks,
said medical sources. The resurgence of dengue during the hurricane season
and spring, when rain is most copious in the Caribbean, is a constant
[factor] that every year costs lives.

[byline: Moises Saab]

